"Castro S.C.D.","Variability of tropical cyclones that have affected Mexico [Variabilidad de los ciclones tropicales que afectan a México]",2010,"Interciencia","35","4",,"306","310",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-79952740152&partnerID=40&md5=70649b0564381a23cf7159a194be2cf8","Centro de Investigaciones Biológicas Del Noroeste (CIBNOR), Mexico; Mar Bermejo 195, col. Playa de Santa Rita, C.P. 23090, La Paz, B.C.S., Mexico","Castro, S.C.D., Centro de Investigaciones Biológicas Del Noroeste (CIBNOR), Mexico, Mar Bermejo 195, col. Playa de Santa Rita, C.P. 23090, La Paz, B.C.S., Mexico","Mexico is vulnerable to the influence of tropical cyclones that develop in the Pacific Northeast and North Atlantic Oceans. During the last years, the destructive force of some of them has led to the idea that their frequency or/and intensity tend to increase due to the global climate change. A greater number of topical cyclones are formed in the Pacific Ocean; however, oceanic and atmospheric circulation displaces them away from the Mexican coasts. That is no the case for the tropical cyclones from the Atlantic Ocean. The analysis over a period of more than 50 years shows that there is no clear increase tendency ofthose meteors, and that the Mexican states with greater impact from tropical cyclones at the Pacific coast are Baja California Sur, Sinaloa, while for the Atlantic coast they are Tamaulipas and Quintana Roo.",,,,,,,,"Andrade, E., Sellers, W., El Niño y sus efectos en la precipitación. Arizona y Nuevo Mexico (1988) J. Climatol, 8, pp. 403-410; Diaz, S., Salinas, C., Hernandez, S., Variability of rainfall l f rom t ropical cyclones in northwestern México and its relation to SOI and PDO (2008) Atmósfera, 21, pp. 213-223; Farfan, L.M., Cortez, M., An observational and modeling analysis of the landfall of hurricane Marty (2003) in Baja California, Mexico (2005) Monthly Weather Review, 133 (7), pp. 2069-2090. , DOI 10.1175/MWR2966.1; Douglas, A., Englehart, P., Modulation of summer rainfall in Mexico by eastern North Pacific tropical storms (1999) Proc. 24th Annual Cliamte Diagnostics and Prediction Workshop, pp. 45-48. , NOAA. US Depar tment of Commerce. Tucson, AZ, EUU; Gray, W., Hurricanes: Their formation, structure and likely role in the tropical circulation (1979) Meteorology over the Tropical Oceans, pp. 155-218. , En Shaw DB (Ed.), Royal Meteorological Society Londres, RU; Landsea, C.W., El Niño-Southern oscillation and the seasonal predictability of tropical cyclones (2000) El Niño and the Southern Oscillation: Multiscale Variability and Global and Regional Impacts, pp. 149-181. , Diaz HF, Markgraf V (Eds.). Cambridge University Press. Cambridge, Inglaterra; Martínez Gutiérrez, G., Mayer, L., Huracanes en Baja California, México y sus implicaciones en la sedimentación en el Golfo de California (2004) GEOS México, 24, pp. 57-64; Pielke Jr., R.A., Landsea, C., Mayfield, M., Laver, J., Pasch, R., Hurricanes and global warming (2005) Bulletin of the American Meteorological Society, 86 (11), pp. 1571-1575. , DOI 10.1175/BAMS-86-11-1571; Reyes, A., Mejía Trejo, S., Perturbaciones tropicales en el Pacífico Este y el campo de precipitación sobre el noroeste mexicano en relación con el fenómeno del ENSO (1991) Int. J. Climatol, 11, pp. 515-528; Tang, B.H., Neelin, J.D., ENSO Inf luence on Atlantic hurricanes via tropospheric warming (2004) Geophys. Res. Lett, 31, pp. L24204; Vitart, F., Anderson, J.L., Sensitivity of Atlantic tropical storm frequency to ENSO and interdecadal variability of SSTs in an ensemble of AGCM integrations (2001) Journal of Climate, 14 (4), pp. 533-545; Webster, P.J., Holland, G.J., Curry, J.A., Chang, H.-R., Atmospheric science: Changes in tropical cyclone number, duration, and intensity in a warming environment (2005) Science, 309 (5742), pp. 1844-1846. , DOI 10.1126/science.1116448; Witney, L., Hoobgood, J., La relación ent re la temperature superficial del maryel máximo de intensidad de los ci